%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22MoviePass%20had%20its%20first%20profitable%20year%20ever%20in%202023%2C%20its%20CEO%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222716%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22moviepass%20logo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F618aee0f23745d001825c58b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221388%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20new%20logo%20for%20MoviePass.%3Cp%3EMoviePass%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMoviePass%20turned%20profitable%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%202023%2C%20CEO%20Stacy%20Spikes%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpikes%20revived%20the%20service%20after%20a%202020%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20app%20has%20surpassed%201%20million%20movies%20seen%20through%20the%20app.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMoviePass%20has%20turned%20a%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20big%20milestone%20for%20any%20startup%2C%20but%20doubly%20so%20for%20MoviePass.%20The%20movie-ticket-subscription%20service%20had%20become%20the%20butt%20of%20jokes%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20when%20it%20famously%20dropped%20its%20monthly%20price%20to%20an%20unsustainable%20%2410%20a%20month%20in%202017%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-story-moviepass-rise-fall-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eled%20to%20a%20predictable%20bankruptcy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20relaunching%20in%202022%2C%20the%20service%20ran%20a%20profit%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20its%20history%20in%202023%2C%20company%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20Stacy%20Spikes%20told%20Business%20Insider%20exclusively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20company%20will%20not%20publicly%20release%20specifics%20about%20what%20it%20earned%20last%20year%2C%20BI%20confirmed%20the%20numbers%20by%20viewing%20internal%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stacy%20Spikes%20in%20a%20blue%20suit%20with%20black%20turtleneck%5C%22