%20and%2For%20making%20your%20life%20miserable.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDitto.%20(But%20make%20sure%20that%20you%20have%20tried%20to%20fix%20the%20situation%20and%20that%20the%20problem%20isn't%20you.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYour%20boss%20is%20unethical.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20one%20is%20a%20three-alarm%20fire.%20If%20your%20boss%20ever%20wants%20you%20to%20do%20something%20you%20think%20is%20morally%20wrong%2C%20talk%20to%20your%20mentors%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20possibly%2C%20HR.%20And%20unless%20these%20folks%20persuade%20you%20that%20what%20your%20boss%20wants%20is%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20actually%20unethical%2C%20don't%20do%20it.%20Keep%20your%20integrity.%20Find%20another%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20here%20are%20some%20%3Cem%3Ebad%3C%2Fem%3E%20reasons%20to%20switch%20jobs%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20don't%20feel%20like%20your%20boss%20appreciates%20you%20enough.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20all%20want%20and%20deserve%20to%20feel%20appreciated%2C%20and%20if%20your%20boss%20is%20taking%20you%20for%20granted%2C%20this%20is%20indeed%20a%20failure%20on%20their%20part.%20But%2C%20by%20itself%2C%20it's%20not%20worth%20quitting%20over.%20If%20you%20otherwise%20enjoy%20your%20job%2C%20try%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-on-one-weekly-meeting-with-boss-mistakes-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efix%20this%20problem%20with%20communication%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(%26quot%3BHello%2C%20Boss!%20You%20didn't%20say%20much%20about%20that%20big%20project%20I%20turned%20in%20last%20week.%20I%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20you're%20happy%20with%20my%20work.%20So%20would%20you%20mind%20if%20I%20asked%20you%20some%20questions%20about%20it%3F%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECo-workers%20at%20the%20same%20level%20are%20getting%20paid%20more%20even%20though%20you're%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20is%20also%20best%20addressed%20with%20communication%2C%20at%20least%20at%20first.%20Ask%20how%20your%20organization%20determines%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-ask-for-a-raise-in-a-recession-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emuch%20to%20pay%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20how%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can%20expect%20your%20compensation%20to%20progress.%20If%20you%20can't%20get%20a%20clear%20explanation%2C%20this%20might%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20become%20a%20good%20reason%20to%20move%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20are%20offered%20a%20similar%20job%20elsewhere%20for%20a%20bit%20more%20money.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20all%20want%20to%20be%20paid%20what%20we're%20worth.%20But%20money%20isn't%20the%20only%20factor%20in%20job%20satisfaction%20(far%20from%20it)%2C%20and%20your%20current%20job%2C%20boss%2C%20and%20organization%20may%20be%20better%20for%20you%20in%20other%20ways.%20Also%2C%20it's%20smart%20to%20avoid%20%26quot%3Blateral%26quot%3B%20moves%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0switching%20to%20substantially%20the%20same%20job%20or%20level%20at%20a%20different%20organization%20or%20team%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20you%20have%20a%20very%20good%20reason%20for%20making%20them.%20So%2C%20here%2C%20too%2C%20try%20communication%20first%3A%20Ask%20what%20you%20need%20to%20do%20to%20get%20a%20raise%20and%2C%20ideally%2C%20a%20promotion.%20Then%20your%20%3Cem%3Enext%3C%2Fem%3E%20outside%20offer%20will%20be%20for%20%3Cem%3Ea%20lot%20%3C%2Fem%3Emore%20money!%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3EShould%20you%20tell%20your%20boss%20you're%20looking%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easier%20to%20get%20a%20job%20when%20you%20have%20one%2C%20so%20if%20you%20have%20a%20choice%2C%20you'll%20probably%20want%20to%20find%20your%20next%20gig%20while%20doing%20your%20current%20one.%20This%20also%20has%20the%20benefit%20of%20allowing%20you%20to%20keep%20your%20salary%20and%20benefits%20while%20you%20look.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(It's%20not%20unethical%20to%20look%20for%20a%20new%20job%20while%20you%20have%20one%2C%20by%20the%20way.%20Your%20current%20boss%20and%20employer%20don't%20own%20you.%20As%20long%20as%20you%20continue%20to%20honor%20any%20commitments%20you%20made%2C%20you%20can%20use%20your%20own%20time%20how%20you%20want%20%E2%80%94%20including%20exploring%20future%20opportunities.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20next%20job%20can%20either%20be%20within%20your%20current%20organization%20or%20outside%20it.%20There%20are%20pros%20and%20cons%20to%20each%2C%20so%20be%20open%20to%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20to%20make%20your%20next%20move%20a%20good%20move%20for%20%3Cem%3Eyou%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20your%20current%20employer%20or%20boss.%20%3Cem%3EYou.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it's%20%3Cem%3Eyour%3C%2Fem%3E%20career%20and%20%3Cem%3Eyour%3C%2Fem%3E%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShould%20you%20tell%20your%20current%20boss%20you're%20looking%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIdeally%2C%20yes.%20In%20general%2C%20it's%20good%20to%20be%20as%20transparent%20as%20possible.%20But%20be%20careful%20how%20you%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20are%20some%20circumstances%20%E2%80%94%20and%20bosses%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20sharing%20the%20news%20ahead%20of%20time%20may%20not%20make%20sense.%20So%20make%20that%20decision%20carefully%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20it%20comes%20time%20to%20actually%20fire%20your%20boss%20%E2%80%94%20to%20tell%20them%20that%20you%20are%20leaving%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0practice%20the%20conversation%20ahead%20of%20time.%20People%20always%20remember%20when%20and%20how%20they%20get%20fired%20%E2%80%94%20including%20people%20who%20are%20bosses.%20So%20you%20want%20to%20do%20it%20as%20decently%20and%20compassionately%20as%20you%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20these%20communications%20can%20be%20tricky%20and%20nuanced%2C%20as%20can%20be%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20job%20while%20still%20doing%20your%20current%20one.%20So%20I'll%20write%20about%20them%20in%20more%20detail%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-to-quit-your-job-for-new-boss-career-growth-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707828095000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ca88126e2e190e71a3b182%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-to-quit-your-job-for-new-boss-career-growth-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20if%20your%20boss%20and%20job%20are%20great%2C%20you%20will%20want%20to%20move%20on%20at%20some%20point.%20Make%20sure%20you're%20doing%20it%20for%20the%20right%20reasons%20and%20avoiding%20%26quot%3Blateral%26quot%3B%20moves.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hblodget%40businessinsider.com%20(Henry%20Blodget)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-to-quit-your-job-for-new-boss-career-growth-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Electoral%20Choices%20Do%20Indian%20Muslims%20Have%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F04205913%2FScreenshot-2022-04-04-at-8.59.07-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%202024%20general%20elections%20are%20looming%20on%20the%20horizon%20some%20Muslim%20elite%20are%20appealing%20to%20Muslim%20community%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fsix-reasons-muslims-look-again-modi-2024-polls-9137422%2F%5C%22%3Egive%20a%20relook%20at%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20claim%20that%20Indian%20Muslims%20are%20not%20being%20discriminated%20against.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20intellectuals%20also%20argue%20that%20BJP%20is%20giving%20special%20attention%20to%20Pasmanda%20Muslims%20and%20the%20Sufi%20Muslims.%20They%20also%20argue%20that%20Muslims%20are%20beneficiaries%20of%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20sch