0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20gentle%2C%20low-impact%20form%20of%20exercise%20may%20help%20keep%20your%20heart%20healthy%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-lower-high-blood-pressure-with-exercise-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower%20your%20blood%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20more%20than%20hitting%20the%20treadmill%2C%20new%20research%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETai%20chi%2C%20a%20Chinese%20martial%20art%20with%20slow%2C%20meditative%20movements%2C%20was%20found%20to%20help%20people%20at%20risk%20of%20hypertension%20to%20reduce%20their%20blood%20pressure%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20published%20February%209%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamanetworkopen%2Ffullarticle%2F2814872%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJAMA%20Network%20Open%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20at%20the%20China%20Academy%20of%20Chinese%20Medical%20Sciences%20worked%20with%20researchers%20from%20several%20universities%20and%20hospitals%20in%20Beijing%20to%20study%20342%20people%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fhypertension%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erisk%20of%20high%20blood%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E%20(known%20as%20prehypertension).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20participants%20ranged%20in%20age%20from%2018%20to%2065%20and%20followed%20an%20exercise%20program%20for%20a%20year.%20Half%20the%20group%20were%20randomly%20assigned%20to%20do%20tai%20chi%2C%20while%20the%20other%20group%20did%20cardio%20exercises%20such%20as%20jogging%20or%20cycling.%20Both%20groups%20did%20their%20assigned%20exercise%20four%20days%20a%20week%20for%20an%20hour%20each%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20six%20months%2C%20participants%20who%20did%20tai%20chi%20saw%20more%20improvements%20in%20their%20blood%20pressure%20than%20the%20cardio%20group.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20tai%20chi%20group%20had%20even%20lower%20blood%20pressure