mantic%20way.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20this%20year%20is%20the%20first%20time%20we're%20celebrating%20as%20parents%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20do%20something%20practical.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20gift%20is%20getting%20a%20will%20prepared%20for%20us.%20Now%20we're%20taking%20inventory%20of%20our%20assets.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20with%20my%20partner%20for%20almost%20a%20decade.%20Over%20the%20years%20we've%20spent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fgifts%2Fvalentines-day-gift-ideas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EValentine's%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%20doing%20a%20lot%20of%20traditionally%20romantic%20things%2C%20like%20eating%20candlelit%20dinners%20at%20our%20favorite%20Italian%20restaurant%20and%20treating%20ourselves%20to%20a%20couples%20massage%20at%20a%20local%20spa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20year%20we're%20celebrating%20our%20first%20Valentine's%20Day%20as%20new%20parents.%20Instead%20of%20buying%20roses%2C%20chocolates%2C%20and%20gifts%2C%20I%20had%20an%20idea%20for%20doing%20something%20more%20practical.%20I%20told%20my%20partner%20that%20this%20year%20I'm%20paying%20for%20us%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-make-a-will-without-a-lawyer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20a%20will%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20idea%20of%20sitting%20down%20with%20a%20third%20party%20and%20mapping%20out%20what%20you%20want%20to%20happen%20when%20you%20die%20might%20not%20seem%20romantic%2C%20I%20disagree.%20The%20key%20to%20a%20strong%2C%20healthy%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-youre-in-a-strong-relationship-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehappy%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20being%20on%20the%20same%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20plan%20everything%20else%20%E2%80%94%20getting%20a%20will%20together%20just%20makes%20sense%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20partner%20and%20I%20often%20map%20out%20activities%20months%20in%20advance%2C%20save%20up%20for%20bucket-list%20vacations%2C%20and%20set%20goals%20we%20can%20work%20on%20together%20weekly%2C%20like%20cooking%20every%20recipe%20in%20our%20favorite%20cookbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20great%20at%20working%20together%20on%20a%20game%20plan%20for%20our%20lives%3B%20it%20made%20sense%20that%20we%20also%20start%20making%20one%20for%20our%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20met%20with%20a%20trusts-and-estates%20attorney%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsederlaw.com%2Fteam%2Ftracy-a-craig%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETracy%20Craig%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20what%20goes%20into%20a%20will%20and%20the%20decisions%20we%20need%20to%20make%20before%20we%20get%20one.%20Here's%20what%20we%20learned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHaving%20a%20will%20helps%20make%20other%20people's%20lives%20easier%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20reasons%20I%20wanted%20my%20husband%20and%20myself%20to%20get%20a%20will%20was%20to%20make%20dealing%20with%20our%20eventual%20deaths%20easier%20on%20my%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20at%20first%20my%20husband%20protested%20the%20idea%20of%20meeting%20with%20an%20estate%20planner%20since%20we're%20both%20only%2035%2C%20Craig%20said%20a%20major%20benefit%20of%20having%20a%20will%20is%20that%20it%20makes%20it%20easier%20for%20the%20people%20in%20your%20life%20once%20you%20die.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20an%20estate%20plan%2C%20or%20one%20that%20doesn't%20work%20properly%2C%20people%20in%20your%20life%20might%20not%20have%20access%20to%20the%20assets%20that%20they%20need%2C%20or%20they%20might%20be%20unable%20to%20make%20decisions%20that%20they%20need%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20solution%20to%20these%20problems%20when%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20will%20can%20be%20expensive%2C%20time-consuming%2C%20and%20invasive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe'll%20need%20to%20pick%20a%20guardian%20for%20our%20child%20in%20the%20will%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20thing%20we%20realized%20we'd%20need%20to%20figure%20out%20for%20our%20will%20is%20who%20would%20take%20care%20of%20our%20daughter%2C%20who's%20almost%201%2C%20if%20we%20both%20die%20while%20she's%20a%20minor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20we%20both%20have%20parents%20who%20are%20alive%2C%20as%20well%20as%20siblings%2C%20not%20noting%20outright%20who%20we'd%20want%20to%20be%20our%20child's%20guardian%20could%20open%20her%20up%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdivorce-share-custody-kids-parenting-plan-time-regret-decision-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecustody%20battle%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20left%20up%20to%20the%20court%20to%20decide%20the%20guardian%20based%20on%20what%20they%20believe%20is%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20the%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20Craig%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20that%20that%20information%20needs%20to%20be%20in%20our%20will%20forced%20us%20to%20begin%20the%20conversation%20about%20who%20her%20guardian%20would%20be.%20Though%20we%20haven't%20agreed%20on%20who%20to%20select%2C%20we've%20set%20a%20deadline%20for%20ourselves%20to%20pick%20someone%20by%20the%20end%20of%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe're%20taking%20inventory%20of%20our%20assets%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECraig%20explained%20that%20there%20are%20other%20decisions%20to%20make%20about%20what%20we%20put%20into%20our%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20we%20have%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimportant-things-to-know-as-the-executor-of-an-estate-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epick%20an%20executor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who'd%20be%20in%20charge%20of%20carrying%20out%20tasks%20like%20paying%20off%20debt%20and%20taxes%20and%20making%20sure%20assets%20and%20property%20are%20distributed%20to%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20we%20need%20to%20assess%20our%20assets%20to%20determine%20what%20would%20go%20in%20the%20will%2C%20such%20as%20bank%20and%20brokerage%20accounts%2C%20real%20estate%2C%20vehicles%2C%20and%20other%20personal%20property%20of%20value%20(including%20furniture%2C%20jewelry%2C%20artwork%2C%20clothes%2C%20and%20technology).%20Craig%20said%20assets%20that%20are%20co-owned%2C%20owned%20in%20a%20trust%2C%20or%20already%20have%20a%20listed%20beneficiary%20don't%20need%20to%20go%20in%20a%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20a%20good%20next%20step%20would%20be%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeet%20with%20our%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20take%20inventory%20of%20our%20bank%20and%20brokerage%20accounts%20so%20that%20we%20can%20assess%20what%20to%20include%2C%20how%20it%20should%20be%20divided%2C%20and%20which%20assets%20already%20have%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20we%20don't%20have%20many%20assets%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20like%20real%20estate%20or%20a%20vehicle%2C%20Craig%20said%20the%20will%20we%20create%20this%20year%20can%20be%20changed%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20make%20small%20changes%2C%20you%20can%20do%20a%20codicil%2C%20which%20allows%20you%20to%20change%20a%20provision%20in%20the%20will%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20usually%20quick%20and%20not%20expensive%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20you%20can%20revoke%20a%20will%20and%20create%20a%20new%20one.%20%26quot%3BA%20benefit%20of%20doing%20that%20is%20that%20when%20you%20die%2C%20your%20will%20is%20public%20record%2C%20so%20if%20you%20don't%20want%20people%20to%20see%20previous%20decisions%2C%20you%20can%20create%20an%20entirely%20new%20will%20and%20revoke%20the%20old%20ones%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGetting%20a%20will%20is%20going%20to%20cost%20about%20%242%2C000%2C%20which%20is%20more%20than%20I%20planned%20to%20spend%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECraig%20told%20us%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busines