t%2Fnews%2Fuae-recruited-alqaeda-assassinations-yemen-report%5C%22%3Erecruiting%3C%2Fa%3E%20al-Qaeda%20members%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fctc.westpoint.edu%2Ftwenty-years-after-9-11-the-jihadi-threat-in-the-arabian-peninsula%2F%5C%22%3Efight%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67945137%5C%22%3Eparamilitary%3C%2Fa%3E%20forces%20against%20Yemeni%20opponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20many%20Yemenis%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20view%20al-Qaeda%20or%20Islamic%20State%20as%20being%20completely%20separate%20from%20those%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20country.%20Rather%2C%20they%20often%20see%20these%20terrorist%20groups%20as%20helping%20to%20reinforce%20the%20status%20quo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20view%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20diametrically%20opposed%20to%20Western%20understandings%20of%20al-Qaeda%20or%20Islamic%20State.%20In%20the%20West%2C%20these%20groups%20are%20framed%20as%20rebels%20seeking%20to%20overturn%20the%20state.%20But%20across%20the%20region%2C%20many%20believe%20these%20relationships%20defy%20simple%20categories%20like%20%E2%80%9Cstate%20versus%20insurgent%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cfriend%20versus%20enemy%E2%80%9D%20because%20terror%20groups%20can%20be%20both%20at%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20Yemeni%20analyst%20articulated%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1080%2F09636412.2023.2250253%5C%22%3Efrustration%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20trying%20to%20explain%20the%20symbiotic%20relationship%20between%20terrorist%20groups%20and%20authoritarian%20leaders%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20easier%20to%20tell%20a%20kid%20that%20Santa%20Claus%20isn%E2%80%99t%20real%20than%20to%20get%20foreigners%20to%20see%20what%20al-Qaeda%20in%20Yemen%20really%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20policies%20are%20backfiring%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Houthis%2C%20America%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20role%20in%20helping%20to%20fuel%20terrorist%20groups%20has%20been%20a%20longstanding%20part%20of%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20messaging.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20a%20decade%20ago%20%E2%80%93%20two%20years%20before%20the%20Houthis%20seized%20the%20Yemeni%20capital%20and%20sparked%20a%20lengthy%20war%20%E2%80%93%20I%20visited%20a%20northern%20town%20where%20there%20were%20several%20large%2C%20freshly%20painted%20murals%20bearing%20the%20statement%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F1354066119837335%5C%22%3Eal-Qaeda%20is%20American%20made%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20asked%20residents%20about%20the%20this%2C%20they%20appeared%20to%20see%20the%20statement%20as%20a%20banal%20declaration%20of%20fact.%20They%20were%20more%20impressed%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnice%20handwriting%E2%80%9D%20than%20the%20message.%20(Like%20the%20banners%20bearing%20the%20%3Cem%3Esarkha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20murals%20used%20a%20red%20barbed-wire%20font%20for%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%E2%80%9D.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Houthis%E2%80%99%20message%20about%20American%20complicity%20in%20terrorism%20resonates%20because%20it%20works%20at%20several%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20gestures%20to%20the%20violence%20unleashed%20by%20the%20US-led%20invasion%20and%20occupation%20of%20Iraq%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F25%2Fas-us-resists-ceasefire-calls-what-is-bidens-endgame-in-gaza%5C%22%3Enear-unconditional%3C%2Fa%3E%20support%20the%20US%20provides%20to%20Israel%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2011%2Fapr%2F05%2Fbritain-let-weapons-be-used-for-repression%5C%22%3Emilitary%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjacobin.com%2F2020%2F03%2Fegypt-prison-state-client-mubarak-al-sisi%5C%22%3Ecarceral%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fpubs%2Fcommentary%2F2013%2F07%2Fhalting-aid-to-egypt-over-military-coup-would-hurt.html%5C%22%3Epolitical%3C%2Fa%3E%20support%20the%20US%20and%20its%20Western%20partners%20provide%20authoritarian%20leaders%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20gets%20at%20the%20profound%20sense%20within%20Yemen%20(and%20across%20the%20region)%20that%20the%20political%20status%20quo%20is%20sustained%20by%20violent%20regimes.%20And%20that%20terrorist%20groups%20like%20al-Qaeda%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20counterterrorism%20interventions%20they%20invite%20%E2%80%93%20are%20part%20of%20how%20those%20regimes%20maintain%20their%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20violence%20the%20Houthis%20use%20to%20sustain%20their%20own%20power%20is%20an%20irony%20that%20should%20not%20be%20lost.%20The%20Houthis%20are%20widely%20despised%20by%20Yemenis%20who%20live%20under%20their%20rule.%20Even%20so%2C%20their%20messaging%20taps%20into%20widespread%20views%20about%20the%20drivers%20of%20regional%20violence%20that%20some%20Western%20observers%20have%20long%20dismissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20complexities%20that%20underpin%20the%20Houthis%E2%80%99%20new%20slogan%20help%20explain%20why%20Western%20policy%20across%20the%20region%20will%20continue%20to%20backfire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPut%20bluntly%2C%20people%20in%20the%20region%20see%20Western%20policymakers%20as%20blind%20to%20their%20historical%20record%20of%20strengthening%20the%20enemies%20they%20come%20to%20fight.%20The%20fact%20that%20Western%20airstrikes%20are%20giving%20the%20Houthis%20a%20legitimacy%20that%20was%20previously%20unimaginable%20is%20ominous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%20for%20Yemeni%20civilians%2C%20the%20Houthis%E2%80%99%20stance%20against%20Israel%20will%20increase%20their%20appeal%20to%20those%20who%20know%20little%20of%20what%20it%20is%20like%20to%20live%20with%20them.%20It%20will%20also%20make%20it%20even%20harder%20for%20Yemenis%20to%20dislodge%20them%20from%20power.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Con