%9CWhether%20you%20join%20work%20early%2C%20or%20take%20a%20break%2C%20you%20will%20be%20judged.%20Whenever%20I%20go%20to%20an%20event%2C%20I%20would%20be%20asked%20who%20is%20looking%20after%20the%20baby.%20I%20think%20the%20judgment%20is%20tremendous.%20I%20know%20that%20my%20son%20is%20my%20joy%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20doing%20the%20best%20for%20him.%20We%20just%20have%20to%20drown%20out%20what%20the%20world%20says%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Radhika.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20urges%20women%20to%20speak%20up%20on%20matters%20of%20maternity%2C%20miscarriage%20or%20just%20asking%20for%20what%20they%20deserve.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20boss%20told%20me%20that%20motherhood%20is%20a%20big%20part%20of%20your%20life%2C%20and%20six%20months%20is%20just%20a%20small%20part%20of%20your%20career%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERadhika%20urges%20women%20to%20have%20big%20dreams%20and%20not%20give%20up%20on%20them.%20She%20shares%20that%20she%20embraced%20motherhood%20at%2039%2C%20and%20manages%20money%20and%20diapers%20with%20equal%20elan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20women%20confused%20about%20how%20to%20manage%20work%20and%20home%20or%20when%20to%20have%20a%20baby%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CDo%20not%20fall%20for%20the%20debate%2C%20and%20do%20things%20as%20per%20your%20time%20and%20will.%20If%20you%20want%2C%20you%20could%20always%20freeze%20your%20eggs%2C%20which%20gives%20you%20an%20option%20of%20having%20kids%20later.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20mom%20gave%20me%20the%20best%20piece%20of%20advice%20on%20motherhood.%20She%20told%20me%20that%20no%20mother%20is%20a%20bad%20mother.%20You%20can%20be%20poor%2C%20rich%2C%20educated%2C%20uneducated%2C%20working%2C%20not%20working%2C%20but%20not%20a%20bad%20mother.%20By%20definition%2C%20a%20woman%20goes%20through%20a%20second%20birth%20to%20have%20a%20child.%20No%20mother%20wants%20less%20than%20the%20best%20for%20her%20child.%20Stop%20telling%20yourself%20that%20you%20are%20a%20bad%20mother%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20sha